Rating: 4
I have made this dish "THE BEST APPETIZER" and party favorite by going the extra mile (which isn't much for anyone who cooks). Instead of using all teryaki sauce for the sate', I use about HALF a cup of teriyaki sauce, and a QUARTER cup of SOY, and HOISIN sauce instead. This cuts down on the real heavy teriyaki taste, and gives it a more subtle, sweeter taste. You can adjust to your own tastes, but this seems to be a happy middle. I personally don't like an all teriyaki taste to Sate's. That's for teriyaki dishes. To give it that REAL THAI RESTUARANT SPICE, add half a teaspoon ground cumin, 1 teaspoon curry powder, half a teaspoon ground pepper, quarter teaspoon salt, and a quarter/to half a teaspoon of 5 spice, to the sate. It leaves you breathless! This is the way I make it everytime, and I get people telling me I need to open a restuarant with this stuff. Also I have found best results have come with marinading it for NO MORE THAN 2 HOURS! The marinade will overpower most of the food.

